RenameTV -- For the batch renaming of TV show files
===================================================

Description
-----------
RenameTV is a simple application to rename files (video episodes of TV shows)
with a standard nameing convention, specified by the user. It uses the XML
services provided by TVRage (http://www.tvrage.com) to fetch show and episode
information to use in the renaming.

Installation
------------
Up-to-date binaries for MS Windows (.exe), Linux (RedHat\SuSE\etc .rpm
Debian\Ubuntu\etc .deb) are available at:
https://github.com/TimJones/RenameTV/downloads

Documentation
-------------
All documentation is available on the GitHub Wiki for RenameTV

Requirements
------------
RenameTV relies on the Qt 4.7.0 version of the QtCore, QtGui, QtXML, and
QtNetwork libraries. To build from source, QtCreator and the QtSDK are needed
also.

